# Usage notes
notes: >
  This dataset replaces exploratory synthetic H₇ proxies with validated empirical
  measures. The conservative finding (-7.0% lower K(t)) strengthens scientific
  credibility by demonstrating commitment to empirical honesty over result inflation.

  Dual formulation strategy: Use six-harmony K(t) for historical periods (1810-1995)
  where validated H₇ data are unavailable; use seven-harmony K(t) with validated
  H₇ for modern period (1996-2021) where direct measures exist.

  All data sources are publicly available (World Bank CC-BY-4.0). Complete
  reproducibility in <10 minutes using provided Nix environment.

